# Line-ending normalization for a cross-platform (Windows + macOS + Linux CI) repo.
#
# Store ALL text files with LF in the repository and check them out as LF on every
# platform. This keeps diffs clean across runners and, importantly, keeps the E-04
# git-fixture harness output byte-stable (CRLF drift would flake the git2-vs-CLI
# cross-check). Rust, Node, and pnpm tooling are all LF-agnostic on Windows.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets: never normalize or attempt text/EOL conversion on these.
*.png binary
*.ico binary
*.icns binary
